    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Equal Employment for All Act of </b> <b>2017</b></p> <p> This bill amends the Fair Credit Reporting Act to prohibit an employer from using a consumer report containing credit information for either employment purposes or for making an adverse employment action.</p> <p>The bill makes exceptions to the prohibition when: (1) the consumer applies for, or currently holds, employment that requires a national security clearance, or (2) a consumer report is otherwise required by law.</p> <p><br> </p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
